 :tx/rationale "Create task: T2-5: Design specification for braid daemon (persistent store process). BACKGROUND: ADR-INTERFACE-004 specifies a library-mode persistent MCP server via rmcp (ArcSwap pattern). A simpler precursor: a Unix domain socket daemon that holds the store in memory and serves CLI commands via IPC. This eliminates the O(n) store rebuild on every invocation. APPROACH: (a) Design the IPC protocol: simple request/response over Unix socket. (b) Daemon lifecycle: braid daemon start/stop/status. (c) CLI auto-detection: if daemon is running, send command via socket; if not, fall back to direct file load. (d) Cache invalidation: daemon watches .braid/txns/ for new files via inotify. ACCEPTANCE: This is a DESIGN SPEC task — produce a design document in docs/design/ with protocol spec, lifecycle management, fallback behavior, and security considerations. No implementation yet. FILE: docs/design/daemon-spec.md. TRACES TO: ADR-INTERFACE-004, INV-INTERFACE-001. DEPENDS-ON: T2-1, T2-2, T2-3."
